UNITED STATES, Appellant, v. 419 BARRELS, More or Less, OF MALT BEVERAGE Contained in Barrels and Vats, etc., Whereof John Hohenadel Brewing Co. is Claimant, Appellee. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. February 11, 1926.) No. 3405. Francis B. Biddle, Asst. U. S. Atty., and George W. Coles, U. S. Atty., both of Philadelphia, Pa., for the United States. William A. Carr and Sidney L. Krauss, both of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.

Before BUFFINGTON, WOOLLEY, and DAVIS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This is one of a group of eases ruled by the decision of this court in Daeufer-Lieberman Brewing Company v. United States, 8 F.(2d) 1. In accordance with the law of that ease, the appeal-is dismissed.
